article.headline: Tennessee Tech 71, Jacksonville St. 56
article.story: COOKEVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Willie Jenkins passed the 1,000-point scoring mark in his first two seasons Thursday, scoring 31 points for Tennessee Tech as it beat Jacksonville State 71-56 on Thursday night. Jenkins also scored the first eight points of the second half as Tennessee Tech (14-10, 9-4 Ohio Valley Conference) pulled within one point after a 32-31 halftime deficit. Tennessee Tech then went on a 9-0 run to take 40-32 lead with 15:45 to play. The run was capped by an Amadi McKenzie free throw. McKenzie and Milone Clark each scored eight points to follow up Jenkins' 31 points for the Golden Eagles. The Gamecocks (7-20, 2-12) were led by Anthony Wilson's 19 points. Walker Russell added 13 and Brandon Davis 12. Tennessee Tech, tied for first in the OVC with Samford, will host the Bulldogs on Saturday. Samford lost to Austin Peay on Thursday.
